		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top">Weight<br clear=all>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 9:59 AM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9956375501592&post=1"><a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9956375501592&num=2&post=1&replyto=9956375501592"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class=sm href="/db/journal2.html?user=1200"><img src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=9956375501592></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=1200"><span id=Scholar>Thayn</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>221 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.21]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Thayn&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Hey, looking at starting a monk and have encountered a problem with my first attempts...<br><br>How does one get any kind of decent weapons and armor (Besides silk) and keep the weight down? I have talked to some monks who say screw it and just compensate with higher AC items.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Is the Monk a Twink's class or are there alternatives?<br><br>Thayn&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Zaloren V'Shnev<br>Enchanter of Innoruuk<br>Master Jeweler<br>Journeyman Smith<br>Vazaelle</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >2 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Jul 20th 3:09 PM2001 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class=sm>IP: Logged</span> | <a class=sm href="/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9956375501592&num=2&post=1&replyto=995656191459"><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=11 width=17> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=995656191459></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=67705"><span id=Sage>Kensuke</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>85 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kensuke&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Monk's are definitely not a twink class, and I can attest to that, as my monk is my primary and first character. <br><br>Essentially, weight is *extremely* important. Higher AC items won't offset the penalties if they push a monk far above their weight limit. <br><br>All cured silk and Wu's armor weigh .1 stone. A foreman's tunic weighs 0. For a list of some good monk items, see my reply to the post above. Those items should keep a monk hovering around 10 or 11 stone. <br><br>Stay away from heavy armors such as patchwork, banded, leather, and raw-hide. And try to use lightweight weapons (Sarnak Enforcer, Essence of Dol, Fighting Baton, Bamboo Bo Stick, etc..) <br><br>While a Monk will probably never have as good an AC as a warrior, Monk's were never designed to take a lot of damage... that's what warrior's were designed for. In fact, in a recent post by a game developer, it's stated that Monk's were given Feign Death primarily to make up for their lack of AC. Monk's, though, were designed to deal a lot of damage quickly. <br><br>While a twinked monk will always do more damage then a non-twinked monk, the same goes for every other twink of every other profession. I always cringe when I see a level 2 monk with a Fungi tunic and a trance staff and knuckle dusters. Where's the fun or pride in that? <br><br>However, non-twinked monks are extremely viable. </p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >1 Replies</td></tr></table><table width="100%"><tr><td class=mhback>&nbsp;</td><td class=mhback >Thread Subject</a></td><td class=mhback>Started by</a></td><td class=mhback>Replies</a></td><td class=mhback>Last Post</a></td><td class=mhback>Rating</a></td></tr><tr class=mdr>
