		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=35651"><span id=Guru>Keyeluke</span></a><b><span id=Guru><br>Guru</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>684 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.61]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Keyeluke&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Nah, Monk doesn't have to be a twink class.&nbsp;&nbsp;I started EQ with a monk, and haven't made an alt other than for banking and trading, and I'm doing fine.  I got a little help from friends when I got in my teens, but not anything too crazy, and in any case I did my first dozen or so levels by saving coppers and running to the bank a lot.  You will be overweight at lower levels, and it won't be that big a deal.  Past your first few levels, weight does start to be an issue - you can't buy enough AC gear to make up for losses from being overweight.  Part of the charm and challenge of the class is managing weight.  People who don't want to deal with that should just become warriors.  Cured silk is great stuff and will suit you fine for a long time.  Start with full cured silk, or Wu's if your tailoring is good enough, and a pair of gem inlaid gauntlets, if you want to have a good setup from the get-go.  As you level up and earn cash, upgrade piece by piece.<br><br>A full set of cured silk, a Sarnak enforcer (1.5 lbs) at 50 pp, Gem Inlaid Gauntlets (1.0) at 100 pp, and some jewelry (whatever u can afford) and you'll be well under limit.  Bags are an issue - Don't know if they nerfed them since, but I used medicine bags at 0.4 lbs each when I was young, instead of dealing with backpacks at 3.0 lbs.  Don't expect to carry more than two or three containers and stay under weight.  I still only carry 3 containers:  a Tink bag (1.0, 10 slot, 100%) a Shralok Pack (0.4, 8 slot, 25%) and a Dusty Ransacker's Pack (0.4, 8 slot, 25%).<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 49th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>Keyeluke<br>Member of Tenacity - Druzzil Ro<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=3&mid=9956375501592&num=2&post=1&mid=9956375501592><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">2 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class3">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
